messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /request/register

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD acceptable: false

- POST acceptable: true

- OPTIONS acceptable: false

- TRACE acceptable: false

- GET acceptable: false

- PUT acceptable: false

- DELETE acceptable: false

- PATCH acceptable: false

Explanation:
- The registerRequest(...) handler method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/request/register", method = RequestMethod.POST). There is no class-level @RequestMapping on RegisterRequestController to add a prefix, so the full path is exactly /request/register.
- The mapping explicitly restricts the handler to RequestMethod.POST, so only POST is acceptable. Following your instruction to decide based on the code (not runtime framework behavior), no other HTTP methods (including HEAD, GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE) are considered acceptable because they are not listed in the mapping and there is no indication of an "all methods" mapping.
